                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There is nothing wrong with the spell itself.  It does what it is suppose to do.  The problem is with the vision that Sony has with the game.  Lets make mobs that hit harder and harder....or scale up faster than players.  The mobs with each expansion is putting out more dps than a player can.  The mobs in tipt/vxed was doing half a groups dps....and guess what....in future expansions that is only going to go <span style="font-weight: bold">UP</span>.  If the game continues this way....THEY CANT ALLOW CHARM (because if you extrapolate...future mobs will hit for more than a couple of groups).  They have now put in a system where they can change the dps of a charm mob.  In this last expansion...it is set to like 40%.  In future expansions when the NPC's dps will further outdistance a player's....that percentage is going to go DOWN.  The problem is that when charm breaks....you still got a mack truck coming after you....soon to be an Abrahms M-1 tank.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">If you want to fix charm, you have to convince Sony to abandone their concept of continually SCALING UP NPCs</span>, because if they continue to do this....that percentage will continue to decrease and it will get to a point where no one will dare charm (because the risk keeps rising without the rewards).  It is game design issue.  Even if they can balance it for this expansion....it will be broken in a few expansions.
<br />

<br />
Charm as we know it is dead.  It cant be fixed because it goes against their game design.
<br />

<br />
Skil</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
