<span style="font-weight: bold">If you want to fix charm, you have to convince Sony to abandone their concept of continually SCALING UP NPCs</span>, because if they continue to do this....that percentage will continue to decrease and it will get to a point where no one will dare charm (because the risk keeps rising without the rewards).  It is game design issue.  Even if they can balance it for this expansion....it will be broken in a few expansions.
<br />

<br />
Charm as we know it is dead.  It cant be fixed because it goes against their game design.
<br />

<br />
Skil</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
people want better gear, and in a sense, that's what the gaem is about. As gear gets better the mobs have to get tougher. Remeber when VS used to be a raid event? remeber when just getting to the Juggs in Seb was a major undetaking? The cycle is- provide mor challenging conttent, have gear available that makes it possible to encounter that content. There is stuff dropping of nothing mobs that in days gone by would have been items what people only could have dreamed of. The game has evlvoed.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Starmist
