                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Charm "Fixes" - assuming we all agree that the risk far outweighs the reward for charming in OoW.
<br />

<br />
There are several things they can change:
<br />

<br />
Mob DPS (currently 25-50% - increase or decrease)
<br />
Charm components (add slow, add snare, add post break mitigation)
<br />
Exp (currently 30% loss - increase or decrease)
<br />

<br />
Risk = chance of dying when charm breaks
<br />
Reward = increased dps or increased exp
<br />

<br />

<br />
1.  Put in a 1% slow component into charm to prevent hasting, increase mob DPS to 50-60% and remove exp penalty.  (same risk, more reward)
<br />

<br />
2.  Keep the altered damage table concept, but raise % damage to 75% and keep exp penalty.  (same risk, more reward)
<br />

<br />
3.  Increase mob DPS to full, put in 1% slow and 1% snare component.  (much more risk, more reward)
<br />

<br />
4.  Put in an upgraded DC that affects higher level mobs, but drops their DPS to 15% normal, with the 1% slow effect built in.  (less risk, less reward)
<br />

<br />
5.  Give back the WoM upgrade originally planned, remove the exp penalty and keep mob DPS where it is.  (less risk, slighly more reward)
<br />

<br />
6.  Have dps mitigation last an extra 2 tics after charm drops, remove exp penalty, leave DPS where it is.  (slightly less risk, slightly more reward)
<br />

<br />

<br />
There are plenty more suggestions out there...  these are just a few.  This would fix charm for OoW, similar fixes are possible for the other "broken" zones like Vxed and Tipt.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
