                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold">Tankchanter</span>,
<br />

<br />
You can try to balance charm for this expansion, but what are you going to do when a future expansion down the road has the mob doing even more dps than this expansion.  The future of this game is that the mob is going to scale up faster than players will.  Even if you couldnt haste the pet now, in a couple of expansions they will still do a full groups damage without haste....again because the mobs dps will go up faster than a player's will.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Starmist</span>
<br />

<br />
I agree with your concept there has to be some character development to make playing this game being meaningful.  I feel there are 2 ways to do this.  
<br />

<br />
The first way is what Sony is doing now.  Scale up the mob, scale up the loot/gear (make it feel like they are improving).  Even though they pass this off as new content....it really isnt.  Doesnt Wos feel like Dreadlands or Burning woods....except the mobs hit harder and we are better equipped...but the concept is the same.  We are basically on a treadmill where the mob is stronger and we are stronger, but the fight is the same.
<br />

<br />
The second way is to cap the dps of players/NPCs and develop new encounters to challenge us...make the fight different (I would love to fight a group of mobs that included healers, nukers and yes, even enchanters)....make there be more puzzles....make there be a coherent story.  The easiest rewards are always better gear/loot.  But what if the gear no longer needs to improve because the mobs arent getting harder.  What if the rewards were more imaginative....like having uniquely designed piece of loot that comes from a certain encounter (like a pointy wizard hat that has graphics and only come from a certain encounter)....or having a matched set of armor that when people see you, they know you have beaten a certain encounter....how about housing....how about trophies to put in the house...how about a new dicipline for a fighter that may put out the same dps, but is different and with graphics to boot....how about gear that usually has no graphics (like the neck piece or ring) having graphics.  Rewards dont always have to be higher and higher HPs/Mana....why cant it be something that makes you stand out among your peers.  More HPs/mana usually translates to bigger and badder mobs (scaling up).
<br />

<br />
WoS is basically the same as Dreadlands with mobs that do more damage and players that have better gear....but the fight is the same.  Sit at a wall somewhere and go out and pull mobs back to group.  It is harder to do number 2.  You have to be creative.  Number 1 route is a basic rehash of a previous zone with different look, harder hitting mobs, and better equipped players.  Number 1 also begins to trivialize alot of classes, like us.
<br />

<br />
Skil</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
