                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If this is the case, they have to give us something to replace charm, because charm was a significant part of an enchanter's arsenal.  Our buffs have to become as necessary as C2 was for groups back in Kunark days, and mez has to become important again, because what else does an enchanter do that isn't already done better by a bevy of other classes?  Heck, maybe they make us the "Rune" masters, masters of damage mitigation with spell and melee shields.  That's a buffing role that at least requires some attention on our part during combat, rather than being a passive buff like KEI or haste that requires absolutely no attention on our parts except every 72 minutes or 4 hours.  If they did that, they should change our names from Enchanter to Abjurer though. <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
How are we balanced if everyone else not only does what we do better than us but does more than what we do?  We aren't.
<br />

<br />
Something similar is happening to rangers and archery, too.  Archery is an incredibly powerful weapon, too powerful for SOE to leave in game as it was so they are changing the focus of ranger damage to melee.  A lot of rangers who for whatever reason disliked archery are happy with this change, but it has left a lot of rangers who were happy with their role as archers unhappy with SOE.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Juneau, Human Fury/27 and Provisioner/34 of Freeport (EQ2/Crushbone)
<br />
Currahee, Erudite Shaman/14 and Alchemist/21 of Freeport (EQ2/Crushbone)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
