                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You guys have got to be kidding. I have personally grouped with chanters in GoD's who have been in 3 person groups and have slaughtered entire zones in Vxed and Tipt for huge amounts of experience and gear/spell farming expeditions. 
<br />

<br />
Any enchanter who is ranting over this change in the face of the obvious overpowering of the CHARM spell does not understand or support the balancing of classes.
<br />

<br />
I 2 box a chanter all the time with my mage(main) and have always gotten 10/1 tells ENC/MAG when LFG.
<br />

<br />
Even with this "Charm" Nerf in place chanters are still very desireable for all groups. 
<br />

<br />
The only differences are:
<br />

<br />
-Rather than waiting 10 minutes for a group you now have to wait 20.
<br />

<br />
-True to not being a pet class... your charm now has the correct ratio of risk and DPS. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal"><span style="font-weight: bold">(chanter runes, 2nd group members root/snare had previously eliminated the "risk" factor of using charm, so the DPS was lowered to match the very low risk associated with using the spell)</span></span></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by magespy on Wed Sep 29, 2004 9:28 am; edited 2 times in total</span></td>
